Class MappableVariable

  • java.lang.Object
    • semsim.SemSimObject
      • semsim.model.SemSimComponent
        • semsim.model.computational.ComputationalModelComponent

            • semsim.model.computational.datastructures.Decimal
              • semsim.model.computational.datastructures.MappableVariable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, Annotatable

    public class MappableVariable
extends Decimal
    A MappableVariable is a Decimal that has a specified input/output designation within the context of a FunctionalSubmodel. It can be mapped to or from another MappableVariable. This class was created to correspond to the <variable> element in CellML models.

    http://www.cellml.org/specifications/cellml_1.1/#sec_model_structure

      • setCellMLinitialValue

        public void setCellMLinitialValue(java.lang.String initialValue)
        Sets the value of the variable at the start of simulation. This property is included to support reading and writing of CellML models; the initial_value attribute in CellML models has a slightly different use than the "startValue" property in the SemSim DataStructure class. In CellML models, the value of a variable that remains constant throughout a simulation can be set using the initial_value attribute. The attribute is also used to set the initial values of state variables. In SemSim, the startValue property is only used to set the initial values of state variables whereas the values of simulation constants are determined by the DataStructure's corresponding Computation class.
        Parameters:
        initialValue - A string representation of the varible's initial value (in the CellML sense)
